{
  "text": "of mesoscale wind fields during the Joint Airport Weather Studies (JAWS) Project. The NASA ADLS was used by [CITATION_1] to measure the wind field in the lee waves of Mount Shasta and by [CITATION_2] to measure the wind field in the vicinity of severe thunderstorms. In 1995, the NOAA ground-based system was installed in a NASA DC-8 aircraft for airborne application (Rothermel et al. 1995) .",
